Breast Cancer Prediction Model

Overview
This project applies machine learning to classify breast cancer tumors as malignant or benign using clinical features from the Breast Cancer Wisconsin dataset.

Methods
- Data preprocessing and cleaning
- Train-test split (80/20)
- Logistic Regression model for tumor classification
- Accuracy evaluation
- Confusion matrix analysis for clinical interpretation

 Results
- Model Accuracy: ~95%
- Low false negatives, high predictive reliability
- Visualized disease distribution using bar charts

Tools
- Python
- pandas
- scikit-learn
- matplotlib 

Significance
This project demonstrates how computational approaches can assist in early detection of breast cancer and support clinical decision-making.
